the constituting of the Vanuatu Multi -Party Parliamentary Synod. The Synod was born out of the realization amongst political leaders that they needed to re-mould the political past in a quest for a better and united present, in turn anticipatin g a better and united future.

We, the political leaders of the twentieth part of the last century, thus commit ourselves through this body to engage in high political debate and discussion.

This vanuatulist tradition provides a means for consensus-building towards 2013, thereby furthering the nation’s march toward greater economic development and social justice under a democratic government.

The Vanuatu NOP Leader vanuatulists and we intend to work together to put differences aside, find common ground and combine the best ideas. We have chosen to work together in accordance with the Vanuatu Constitution. Any need to change the constitution must be done in keeping with its intent. We aim to ensure, that no matter who wins the next election, the three branches be kept in balance. That includes maintaining one of our country’s greatest strengths — our party system.
